Probatus with a dative has an adjectival sense: so Verr. ii. 17, si cuiquam yeueri homiuum probatus sit: and the superlative tibi probatissimos, Ligar. §32 Scamander was ‘acceptable to' his master. Fabricius had tested him and found him not wanting: he ‘vouched’ for him. Op. Lucil. ap. Nou. 437, tuam probatam mi et spectatam adules- centiam: Tac.
